C language installation - Windows

Download "Code Blocks", ( Windows 64 bit (including compiler) ) from http://www.codeblocks.org/downloads/binaries/.

Select:
New project > Console application > everything else should be self explanatory.
After setup click on the left side > Sources > open main.c

Paste the code:

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main()
{
    printf("Hello world!\n");
    printf("Hello\n");
    printf("World");
    printf("!\n");

    return 0;
}

-----------------------
To run the code click "Build and run".

Output:
Hello world!
Hello
World!
